In [18]:
# Get rid of accent marks
import unidecode 
byePunctuation=lambda x: unidecode.unidecode(x)
              # Define una función lambda que recibe un texto x y le aplica unidecode.unidecode(x).
              # unidecode.unidecode(x) convierte cualquier carácter especial en su equivalente sin acento
covid_py_w['LOCATION']=covid_py_w['LOCATION'].apply(byePunctuation) #data covid
provmap['LOCATION']=provmap['LOCATION'].apply(byePunctuation) #data map
In [19]:
# replacing dashes and multiple spaces by a simple space
covid_py_w['LOCATION']=covid_py_w.LOCATION.str.replace("\-|\_|\s+","",regex=True)
provmap['LOCATION']=provmap.LOCATION.str.replace("\-|\_|\s+","",regex=True)

import folium

map1=covid_py_map[covid_py_map.COVID_Q_NAMES_2021=='1 hotSpot']
map2=covid_py_map[covid_py_map.COVID_Q_NAMES_2021=='2 coldOutlier']
map3=covid_py_map[covid_py_map.COVID_Q_NAMES_2021=='3 coldSpot']
map4=covid_py_map[covid_py_map.COVID_Q_NAMES_2021=='4 hotOutlier']

map_layers = map1.explore(
    color="red",
    tooltip=False,  # hide tooltip
    popup=["LOCATION"], 
    name="HotSpot" 
)
map2.explore(
    m=map_layers, # notice
    color="skyblue",
    tooltip=False,
    popup=["LOCATION"],
    name="ColdOutlier"
)
map3.explore(
    m=map_layers,
    color="blue",
    tooltip=False,
    popup=["LOCATION"],
    name="ColdSpot",
)

map4.explore(
    m=map_layers,
    color="darkorange",
    tooltip=False,
    popup=["LOCATION"],
    name="HotOutlier",
)

folium.TileLayer("CartoDB positron", show=False).add_to(map_layers)  # use folium to add alternative tiles
folium.LayerControl(collapsed=True).add_to(map_layers)  # use folium to add layer control
